title: Lincoln Assassinated
subtitle: A great travesty
on-arrival: {!
Q.moderate_strength -= 5;
Q.radical_strength += 5;
Q.president = "Johnson"
!}
tags: event
view-if: year = 1865 and month = 4

President Lincoln was assassinated by John Wilkes Booth while watching a play at Ford's Theatre. Government forces are currently on the lookout for the assassin, but now Lincoln's vice president, southern sympathiser Andrew Johnson, is president, much to our dismay.
